Hello guys,
I am working on my extension and I am struggling with the API as I have no idea what's the best way to implement my use case - perhaps you could give me some help?

Basically I am trying to offer almost the same experience of having a Markdown document with preview opened on the side: as you type into the new document, you get the preview updated.

Thing is that actually this feature you're offering it's working only if the file is saved on the disk. I would like to offer the same experience for untitled files. What would be the best way to accomplish this?

The way I was trying to do this is to install a global handler on the client side to all document changes event and then try to verify if my preview is somehow opened:

```javascript
  workspace.onDidChangeTextDocument((changeEvent) => {
    if ((changeEvent.document.languageId === 'apiblueprint' || changeEvent.document.languageId === 'swagger') &&
      workspace.textDocuments.some((doc) => doc.isUntitled && doc.fileName.includes('parseResult.json'))
    ) {
      
    }
  });

```
Basically checking that:
1. The changed document opened has my language ID
2. There's a preview opened (using the untitled filename I am creating)

but to be honest it does not seem to be that clever to me.

My extension is a server/client thing, so I can work on both sides to make this happen.

- VSCode Version: 1.11.1
- OS Version: macOS Sierra 10.12.3

Steps to Reproduce:

1. Create a JavaScript class like the following:
```javascript
class Test {
	/**
	 * A test method.
	 * @param {Object.<string, string>} obj An object.
	 */
	testMethod(obj) {
		console.log(obj);
	}
}
```
2. Hover over the method: you can see that the `obj` parameter is declared as type `any`, even though according to According to [this](http://usejsdoc.org/tags-type.html) it should be declared as `Object` or `Object.<string, string>`. 
![Image of Bug](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/13303021/24824955/3e139af4-1bca-11e7-8df6-e6d4d9f1e6fa.png)

- VSCode Version: 1.11.1

